  <!ENTITY dhsection   "<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>">
  <!ENTITY dhucpackage "<refentrytitle>OBXCTL</refentrytitle>">
  <!ENTITY dhpackage   "OBXCTL">
]>

<refentry>
  <refmeta>
    &dhucpackage;

    &dhsection;
  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose>Pass actions to openbox. </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>
      <arg choice="Opt">--help</arg>
      <arg choice="Opt">-d DISPLAY</arg>
      <arg choice="Opt">--</arg>
      <arg choice="Opt">FILE</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>obxctl is a tool that reads XML data from FILE, or STDIN if no FILE is specified or FILE is -, and passes them on to openbox for execution.</para>

    <para>Internally, it sends an XEvent to the root window, that tells openbox to read from a named pipe located at $XDG_CACHE_HOME/openbox/$DISPLAY. Then it writes the contents of FILE (or STDIN) to the pipe.</para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <para>These are the possible options that <command>&dhpackage;</command> accepts:</para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--help</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show a summary of the options available.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-d</option> DISPLAY</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Specify the X display to use.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para>Similar to <command>xprop</command>,
      you may pass one or more property names to have
      <command>&dhpackage;</command> limit its output to only the properties
      requested.</para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>SEE ALSO</title>

    <para>openbox (1), openbox-session(1), openbox-gnome-session(1),
      openbox-kde-session(1).</para>

  </refsect1>
</refentry>

